### Storage Module HTTP Tests


### 

@accessToken = {{accessToken}}
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000


### Upload File

# @name UploadFile

# Note: In VS Code REST Client, use actual file path

POST {{baseUrl}}/storage/upload?bucket=test-bucket HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Test file content for upload testing
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

> {%
{% 
    client.global.set("fileKey", response.body.data.key);
    client.log("File Key: " + response.body.data.key);
%}


### List Files

GET {{baseUrl}}/storage/files?prefix=&limit=10&page=1 HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### Get File Metadata

GET {{baseUrl}}/storage/file/{{fileKey}}?bucket=test-bucket HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### Download File

GET {{baseUrl}}/storage/download/{{fileKey}}?bucket=test-bucket HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### Generate Presigned URL

GET {{baseUrl}}/storage/presigned/{{fileKey}}?bucket=test-bucket&expirySeconds=3600 HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### Delete File


### 

DELETE {{baseUrl}}/storage/file/{{fileKey}}?bucket=test-bucket HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
